Package org.ggp.base.apps.research

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Aggregation<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    Aggregation is a way of storing data about an unordered collection, mapping each element to an associated data object, and then visualizing the data by sorting the elements by their associated data and printing out the sorted list.
    Counter
    Counter is a convenience class for tracking a count.
    FrequencyTable
    FrequencyTable is an aggregation that maps keys to weighted averages.
    Histogram
    Histogram is a way of visualizing an unordered collection with repeated elements, by mapping each element to the number of times that it appears.
    MatchArchiveProcessor
    MatchArchiveProcessor is a utility program that reads in serialized match archives, like those available at GGP.org/researchers, and runs some computation on every match in the archive.
    WeightedAverage
    WeightedAverage is a convenience class for tracking a weighted average.
